How are ratings calculated?
To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

マザーボード TUF GAMING B660M-PLUS D4 メモリ Team ARGB DDR4 3600Mhz 16G×4 CPUクーラー Deepcool AS500 PLUS グラフィックボード MSI RTX3060 という構成で自作しました。 今までで３台PCを自作してきましたが、すべてRyzenCPU(Ryzen7 5800X Ryzen9 3950X 5900X)で、B550とRTX3060での使用でした。... See more
マザーボード TUF GAMING B660M-PLUS D4 メモリ Team ARGB DDR4 3600Mhz 16G×4 CPUクーラー Deepcool AS500 PLUS グラフィックボード MSI RTX3060 という構成で自作しました。
今までで３台PCを自作してきましたが、すべてRyzenCPU(Ryzen7 5800X Ryzen9 3950X 5900X)で、B550とRTX3060での使用でした。
特に不具合もなく３台ともゲームや動画・画像編集等そつなくこなしていましたが、少し気になっていたのはWindows１１にしてからのクリックしたときの微妙な遅延の発生や一部のゲームやアプリでのわずかなカクつきがありましたが、そこまで酷い症状ではなかったので「個体差」なのだろうと気にしていませんでした。
そんな中、インテル１２世代CPUの紹介動画やレビューなどを見て以前のCPUよりも高速・高性能になったことを知って興味を持ち、今回初めてインテルCPUでPC自作をすることにしました。
細かいデータ内容等は、他の皆さんが動画やレビューをネットにあげていらっしゃるので、ここでは説明しませんが、素人目からしてまず体感できて驚いたのが、RyzenPCとくらべてPCの立ち上がりが早くなったことと、いろいろなクリックや動作に遅延がほとんど無くなり、あらゆる反応が高速でほぼ確実に動作するようになったことです。(同じタイミングで２台を動作させてみた。)
ゲームでは3060でも十分すぎるくらいで、カクつきも無くなり、全体的に「違和感」が無くなった感じです。(WQHD2560×1440p 高設定での使用。)
今回からインテルCPUでの使用で、PコアとEコアのハイブリッド使用になったおかげもあるのか、通常アイドル時や今までRyzenPCで使用していた同じ動画編集ソフト等の消費電力が下がったのも、電気代節約に貢献できてとても良いです。
CPUに関してはメリットしかありませんが、しいて言えばマザーボード等の周辺機器が高価なのがネックになりますね。今後は安価にはなっていくとは思いますが、個人的に言えば、高価なだけの「価値」は十分にあると思いました。
今度はインテルでのハイエンドPCを作ってみようかな、とも思わせるようなCPUでした。
マザーボード TUF GAMING B660M-PLUS D4 メモリ Team ARGB DDR4 3600Mhz 16G×4 CPUクーラー Deepcool AS500 PLUS グラフィックボード MSI RTX3060 という構成で自作しました。

今度はインテルでのハイエンドPCを作ってみようかな、とも思わせるようなCPUでした。 Motherboard TUF GAMING B660M-PLUS D4 Memory Team ARGB DDR4 3600Mhz 16G×4 CPU Cooler Deepcool AS500 I made my own with the configuration of PLUS graphic board MSI RTX3060.
Until now, I have made 3 PCs myself, but they were all RyzenCPU (Ryzen7 5800X Ryzen9 3950X 5900X), and they were used in B550 and RTX 3060 .
There were no problems in particular, and all three were doing games, movies/image editing, etc., but what I was a little worried about was the occurrence of subtle delays when I clicked on Windows 11 and some There was a slight stir in the game and app, but since it wasn't such a terrible symptom, I didn't care if it was an “individual difference”.
Under such circumstances, I was interested to know that it became faster and higher performance than previous CPUs by watching introduction videos and reviews of Intel 12th generation CPUs, and I will make my own PC with Intel CPUs for the first time this time I decided to.
Other people are posting videos and reviews on the net, so I won't explain it here, but I was surprised to experience it first from an amateur's eye, compared to Ryzen PC The fact that the PC starts up faster, there is almost no delay in various clicks and actions, and all reactions work almost reliably at high speed. (I tried operating two units at the same timing.)
In the game, even 3060 is more than enough, and there are no more cocktails, and the overall feeling of “incongruity” has disappeared. (For use on WQHD2560×1440p high settings.)
Is it due to the hybrid use of P-core and E-core when used on Intel CPUs from now on, or consumption of the same video editing software that has been used in Ryzen PC until now, when idle or until now It is also very good that the power drops can contribute to saving electricity bills.
There are only advantages in terms of CPU, but in other words, peripheral devices such as motherboards are expensive is the bottleneck. I think it will become cheaper in the future, but personally speaking, I thought that there is enough “value” just for being expensive.
It was a CPU that reminds me of making a high-end PC with Intel this time.

Eradication
3.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
パワーフール感が、追記星３で優しいかもThe feeling of power fool may be gentle with the postscript star 3
Reviewed in Japan on November 24, 2021
20220306追記 最近ゲーム中のCPU温度見てみたら15度前後高い、FPUテストしてみたら、OCなしで91度、前は75度だったのに！... See more
20220306追記

最近ゲーム中のCPU温度見てみたら15度前後高い、FPUテストしてみたら、OCなしで91度、前は75度だったのに！
調べてみたら、Intel第12世代CPUのIHSはソケット圧で歪むという問題があるらしい、自分が当たってしまいました。写真の通り、シリコングリスが全部真ん中らへんへ集中していました。横からは写真うまく取れないけど、1°くらい曲がってしまいました。M4ワッシャー入れてみました、FPU81度にさがりましたが、75よりたかい、変形したせいかな。Intelとマザボ両方の問題かと思われますが。

いまのところ、性能について満足しているが、耐久性についてはかなり心配になってきました、5年くらい使いたいですけどね。

------------------------------------------

今のパソコン（4世代）が若干重く感じてきたので、プラスFF14のパッチ6.0に向けて、パーツ更新しようと。12700k、MSI z690 pro a DDR4、Ｇ.skill DDR4-4000 c18, 2x16GB で構成した、グラフィックボードはGTX1080のまま（あまりみてないけど、最近のグラボ値段おかしくない？）
4k環境では、最高画質は無理のままでした、カスタマー設定でなんとか・・・しかし、最低FPSはかなり改善されたような、あまり重く感じなくなった。ゲームはこれでよし、次世代グラボ待つことにした。

普段作業として、たちあがるのがめちゃくちゃ早くなったし、古いパソコン4kでExcelは重く感じたけど、快適になった！ほかにいろいろのソフトもかなり早くなった、さすがに8世代飛ばした感はある、（笑）。

遊びとして、オーバークロックやってみた、MSIのマザボでTurbo Ratio Offsetがありまして、軽くオーバークロックするならこれでオーケー、ｐコーア、eコーア全部+3でＣＰＵＺでシングルコーアなんと850点、マルチは1万突破！電圧は自動で1.35vでした。CPUクーラーはＤ15、ケースの問題でファン一つしかいれていない、コーア全部+1でＦＰＵ80℃前後、+3はBiosの問題かなかわからないけど、うまく走れない。Gear1でメモリもそのまま4000 c18になるし、かなり安定している。なかなか楽しかった。普段使いはオーバークロックしないけど。

あと、夜中に買い物はよくない、めっちゃ思ったけど、なんでＫＦにしなかった（笑）。

日本語下手くそでごめんよ。

postscript When I looked at the CPU temperature in the game recently, it was around 15 degrees high, and when I tested the FPU, it was 91 degrees without OC, and 75 degrees before!
When I looked it up, there seems to be a problem that the IHS of the Intel 12th generation CPU is distorted due to socket pressure, and I hit it. As shown in the picture, all the silicone grease was concentrated in the middle. I can't get a picture from the side well, but it's bent by about 1°. I tried putting an M4 washer, it hit 81 degrees FPU, but it was tougher than 75, probably because it was deformed. I think it's a problem with both Intel and Mazabo.

Right now, I'm satisfied with the performance, but I'm pretty worried about durability, and I want to use it for about 5 years.

—

I feel that the current PC (4th generation) is a little heavy, I'm going to update parts for patch 6.0 of Plus FF14. 12700k, MSI Z690 Pro A DDR4, G.Skill DDR4-4000 C18, 2x16GB, the graphic board is still GTX1080 (look too much (No, but isn't the recent grabo price strange?)
In a 4k environment, the maximum image quality remained unreasonable, I managed to do it with the customer settings... but the minimum FPS seemed to be considerably improved, and it didn't feel too heavy. This is the game, and I decided to wait for the next-generation Grabo.

As a normal work, it became insanely fast to get up, and Excel felt heavy on my old PC 4K, but it became comfortable! In addition, various software has also become much faster, and there is a feeling that 8 generations have been skipped as expected (laughs).

As a play, I tried overclocking, there is a Turbo Ratio Offset in MSI's Mazabo, and if you want to overclock lightly, this is OK, p All cores and e-cores are +3, single cores in CPUZ have 850 points, and multi surpassed 10,000! The voltage was automatic at 1.35v. The CPU cooler is D15, only one fan is added due to a case problem, all cores are +1, FPU around 80° C, +3 is a Bios problem, but I can't run well. On the Gear1, the memory is 4000 c18 as it is, and it is quite stable. It was a lot of fun. I don't overclock for everyday use.

Chiaramente consiglio di associare la CPU di Intel a una buona scheda madre con chipset Z690 o Z790 e se avete soldi da spendere ad una buona scheda video serie RTX. Great processor, not good quality-price with remarkable gaming performance. Stable and high-performance processor. Without going down as usual on considerations and technical aspects, which I leave to others, I recommend the Core i7-12700K to those who are preparing to assemble a high-profile gaming platform, but, at the same time, to all those users who look at productivity and performance in the multi-core environment. As far as the comparison with AMD is concerned, this model clashes with the Ryzen 9 5900X, very good, but with a higher cost than the Intel proposal. Clearly I recommend combining the Intel CPU with a good motherboard with a Z690 or Z790 chipset and if you have money to spend with a good RTX series video card.

R. G.
4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
Excellent processor
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 27, 2022
There is not too much I can say about this processor which has not already been said in countless reviews on the internet. This processor is an extremely capable bit of silicon that should provide a good level of computing for several years. This version of the processor...See more
There is not too much I can say about this processor which has not already been said in countless reviews on the internet. This processor is an extremely capable bit of silicon that should provide a good level of computing for several years. This version of the processor arrives in a card box, within which is a plastic case that holds the processor. It is nothing fancy, and in fact appears a little under whelming when you consider the potential of the product safely held by the plastic. Once the prcessor is removed form the packaging, fitting to a motherboard is very straight forward, although care must be taken when placing the chip in the socket so that no pins on the board are bent, and that the chip is orientated correctly in relation to the socket. Fit a good cooler and you are set for a new level of speed. In my case, I finally upgraded from an older (2014) i7 4770k and the difference for me is very obvious. Everything just seems to happen more quickly now. This has been a worthwhile upgrade for me. It was expensive, since I had to replace the motherboard and memory, get a new cooler and added a couple of NVME drives. But it will last me for years before I consider another update. A very good processor that could revolutionise your computing experience.
There is not too much I can say about this processor which has not already been said in countless reviews on the internet. This processor is an extremely capable bit of silicon that should provide a good level of computing for several years.

This version of the processor arrives in a card box, within which is a plastic case that holds the processor. It is nothing fancy, and in fact appears a little under whelming when you consider the potential of the product safely held by the plastic.

Once the prcessor is removed form the packaging, fitting to a motherboard is very straight forward, although care must be taken when placing the chip in the socket so that no pins on the board are bent, and that the chip is orientated correctly in relation to the socket.

Fit a good cooler and you are set for a new level of speed. In my case, I finally upgraded from an older (2014) i7 4770k and the difference for me is very obvious. Everything just seems to happen more quickly now.

This has been a worthwhile upgrade for me. It was expensive, since I had to replace the motherboard and memory, get a new cooler and added a couple of NVME drives. But it will last me for years before I consider another update.

A very good processor that could revolutionise your computing experience.

Ein stolzer Preis für eigentlich veraltete Technologie (10nm - wir stehen jetzt bei 7nm und in Kürze bei 5nm, nur Intel bekommt das nicht hin - 7nm wäre der halbe Verbrauch bei gleicher Rechenleistung), der Prozessor bringt es deshalb auf wahnsinnige 180W (lt. Intel Ark), was bei meinem luftgekühlten PC schon zu einem deutlichen Lärmpegel führt, da ich keine Spiele spiele sondern Grafiken und ähnliches mache, ist das "aufheulen" aber zeitlich begrenzt und eine Flüssigkühlung auch kein Thema.
Die Idee mit den stromsparenden Cores scheint ganz gut, der PC langweilt sich ja meistens, leider habe ich keinen Zugriff auf Laborequipment um mal den tatsächlichen Verbrauch zu messen - das ist mit "normalen" Messgeräten leider unmöglich.

I treated myself to the brand new processor - there are no many alternatives for the desktop in the class - 2 sockets or even just one scaleable/epyc would have missed the mark.
A proud price for actually outdated technology (10nm - we are now at 7nm and soon at 5nm, only Intel can't do that - 7nm would be half the consumption for the same processing power), so the processor has an insane 180W (according to Intel Ark), which already leads to a significant noise level in my air-cooled PC because I don't play games but do graphics and the like, the “howling” is limited in time and liquid cooling is also not an issue.
The idea with the power-saving cores seems quite good, the PC usually gets bored, unfortunately I don't have access to laboratory equipment to measure the actual consumption - unfortunately that's impossible with “normal” measuring devices.
Otherwise, there is not much to say, the quality of the CPUs is out of question at Intel.
All in all, 4 stars, even considering that my first car cost less than the CPU, but the comparison seems to be a limp.

In idle sta tranquillo sui 28° e giocando non supera i 60°. Direi ottimo. What can I say, I've always been a fan of Intel, and I've always equipped my PCs with their CPUs.
With stock values, it heats a little too much but it is enough to undervolt ad oc and the problem is solved while maintaining the same performance.
If you want to use it in OC, I recommend a nice performing AIO or a custom liquid dissipation system.
I'm running it in OC with adaptive peaks up to 5.4ghz in P-core and 5.1ghz in E-core, with 360mm CORSAIR H150i lcd cooler and the temps do not exceed 75° in FULL LOAD (benchmark test). In idle it is quiet on 28° and playing it does not exceed 60°. I'd say great.

Alder Lake is a game-changer. Having E cores helps save power consumption while still performing quite well. Temps are cool at idle, and around 80C at 100%.

Cinebench benchmarks are just below a $6.3k (!!!!!) CPU. I bought it at MSRP and worth the money. Even better if you can find it at discount.

Something to keep in mind: it was difficult to find AIOs at the time of the review because you have to find a cooler that supports the new LGA 1700 socket. Most brands have some aftermarket support - you can order for free or buy brackets or screws. But check their inventory before ordering.

Last note: I went from an i5-4670K so this is a massive upgrade for me. But so worth it to anyone who cares about tech to get since it features new core tech and simply amazing performance for the money.

I just wish the GPU manufacturers could keep up and sell to individuals or small businesses at LOW VOLUME because to get an RTX 3090 today costs more than 3k EUR which is frankly ridiculous.

Decided to jump in the Alder Lake CPUs from Intel, to upgrade from the 4 year old Coffee Lake i7-8700k CPU. My computer is used as an all-in-one machine for gaming, work, editing, entertainment.
